To design and develop a Movie Showcase website using HTML and CSS that displays movie details such as movie name, genre, description, and categorized movie lists with an attractive and user-friendly design. 
 
Procedure – Movie Showcase Website (With CSS) 
Step 1: Creating the Basic HTML Structure 
The project was started by creating HTML files using the 
<!DOCTYPE html> 
declaration along with <html>, <head>, and <body> tags. Step 2: Setting Website Title 
Inside the <head> section, the title “Movie Showcase” was added using the 
<title> tag. 
Step 3: Linking CSS File 
A separate CSS file was created and linked using: 
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"> 
This improves the design and appearance of the website. Step 4: Designing the Home Page 
The main page includes: 
 <h1> for website title 
 
 <p> for introduction 
 <a> tags for category navigation 
<hr> for separation Step 5: Displaying Movie Details 
Each movie section includes: 
 <h2> for movie title 
 <p> for genre  <p> for description 
 
<hr> for separation Step 6: Applying CSS Styling CSS was used to: 
 Add background colors 
 Improve font styles 
 Style buttons 
 Add hover effects 
 Improve layout alignment 
Step 7: Final Testing 
The project was tested to ensure: 
 Proper navigation between pages 
 
 Clean layout 
Attractive design 
Responsive button effects 
 
Working 
The browser loads the HTML structure.
The CSS file enhances the visual appearance.
 Navigation links connect all pages. 
 Headings highlight movie names. 
 Styled buttons improve user interaction. 
 Horizontal lines separate content clearly. 
